Hoglins will run if in contact with warped fungi, respawn anchors, or nether portals.

Which can be a golden sword, a crossbow, or random golden armor.

Adult piglins are neutral and babies are passive.
Adult piglins can be bartered with.
Piglins will run from placed soul fire and soul fire items.
Piglins will not attack the player if they're wearing a piece of golden armor.
Piglins will turn into zombified piglins if in the Overworld or the End after 15 seconds.
Piglins will occasionally hunt hoglins and wither skeletons, with a 10% chance of doing a ”victory dance” after killing a hoglin by jumping and running around the area.
Up to 3 baby Piglins can ride on a baby hoglin at one time. The top one(s) piggy-back.
Piglins will also hold, but not barter for, gold items (golden carrots, golden armor, etc.)
Piglins will attack any player that has opened a chest in the bastion, mined the nether gold ore, or mined a gold block in front of them.

20 (when killed by a player or tamed wolf)

Piglin brutes are tougher and stronger variants of piglins.
Piglin brutes are always hostile unlike other piglins.
Piglin brutes attack the player even when they're wearing golden armor.
Piglin brutes do not run away from placed soul fire and soul fire items.
Piglin brutes will not hunt hoglins.
Piglin brutes will turn into zombified piglins if in the Overworld or the End after 15 seconds.

Striders can walk on top of the surface of lava.
Striders can be saddled, and can be controlled with warped fungi on a stick.
Striders are attracted by warped fungi.
Striders can be bred using warped fungi.
Striders shiver and turn purple outside of lava.
Striders are damaged by rain and water.

Rotten Flesh (1–3)
5 (when killed by a player or tamed wolf)

Zoglins and baby zoglins attack all nearby mobs and players except for creepers and other zoglins.
Zoglins are incapable of breeding.
Unlike baby hoglins, do not play with baby piglins.
Piglins will flee from zoglins if unengaged in combat.
Zoglins do not flee from warped fungi.

Reduced the maximum distance a bee can wander away from its home hive when randomly wandering to around 22 blocks.
Grow up and count down their breeding cool down when inside a beehive.
Cows can now be milked in Creative mode.

Enderman now spawn in the Nether more commonly again, especially in warped forests.
Enderman now pick up nylium, roots, and fungi variants.
Enderman no longer pick up netherrack.
Ghasts' sounds are now heard at a shorter range.

Mooshrooms can now be milked in Creative mode.
Mushroom stew and suspicious stew can now be obtained in Creative mode.

Parrots imitate hostile mobs less often.
Parrots no longer randomly imitate hostile mobs when gamemode is on Peaceful.

Snow golems are now damaged by splash and lingering water bottles.
Snow golems now drop carved pumpkin when they are sheared.
When any villager is struck by lightning, the witch it is converted to will no longer despawn, regardless of whether the villager had been traded with or not.

Farmer villagers can now put seeds in the composter to create bone meal.
Farmers can now use bone meal to grow crops.
Withers can now be summoned using soul soil in the base.

Zombie pigmen were renamed to "zombified piglin" and given a new model and texture.
Zombified piglins now also spawn rarely in crimson forests.
Zombified piglins no longer attack players who have not attacked a zombified piglin.
Zombified piglins now stop being angry if the targeted player dies nearby. (But only if gamerule forgiveDeadPlayers is set to true)

Ancient debris can be found in the Nether, but are extremely rare.
Never generates exposed to air, and is most common between levels 8 and 22.

Ancient debris can be smelted into netherite scrap.
Ancient debris can be used in blast-resistant doors.

Blocks of netherite can be used decoratively, as a storage block for netherite ingots, or as part of a blast-resistant wall/door.
Blocks of netherite can be used in the base of a beacon.

Lodestones can be used in any dimension.

Basalt can be found in the Nether making up basalt pillars within soul sand valley biomes.
Basalt deltas contain an abundance of basalt blocks, as it is one of the main blocks that form the biome.
Basalt is formed when lava flows over soul soil next to blue ice.

Basalt can be used as a decorative block.
Basalt can be crafted into polished basalt.
Polished basalt can be used as a decorative block.

Blackstone can be found in large patches in basalt deltas.
Blackstone can be found on all nether biomes at the lava level.

Blackstone can be used as a substitute for cobblestone in certain crafting recipes.
Blackstone can be made into slabs, stairs and wall variations.
Blackstone can be crafted into polished blackstone.
Blackstone's bottom texture is changed with the top texture.

Warped wart blocks can be used as a decorative block.

Twisting vines grow upward.

Respawn anchors explode if used in the Overworld or End.
Respawn anchors can be charged with a dispenser.

Fire lit on soul soil appears as soul fire.
The player does not sink and is not slowed when walking on soul soil.
Soul soil can be used to summon the Wither.

Soul fire deals damage at a rate of 2 per second as opposed to the 1 per second of regular fire.
Soul fire repels piglins.
Soul fire has a hitbox.

Beacons can now have a base composed of blocks of netherite.
Beacons can now use netherite ingots as a fuel.
Bells will now ring when hit by any projectile.

Bone blocks now generate as part of nether fossils in soul sand valleys.
Bone blocks now have their own sound, instead of using the stone sound.
Campfires now ignite when hit by any burning projectile.

Dispensers can now saddle pigs, striders, and tamed horses, donkeys and mules.
Dispensers can now put horse armor on tamed horses.
Dispensers can now put carpets on tamed llamas.
Dispensers can now put chests on tamed llamas, donkeys, and mules.
Dispensers can now shear mooshrooms and snow golems.
Dispensers now display a new death message: [player] went off with a bang due to a firework fired from [item] by [player/mob]

Fire now has a proper hitbox (1⁄16 blocks).
Fire can no longer be put out by swords or tridents in Creative mode, akin to other blocks, and can be modified via the debug stick.
Fire now has loot tables.
Flower pots now have a bottom texture.
Gravel now generate naturally in all nether biomes at the lava level.

Jigsaw blocks can now have one of 12 orientations.
Now have a new "Keep Jigsaws" option that controls whether jigsaw blocks in the resulting structure after using "Generate" will remain jigsaw blocks or be replaced by their "Turns Into" block.
Defaults to "ON".

Nether wart blocks now generate as a part of huge crimson fungi.
The texture of Nether wart block is slightly changed.

Using bone meal on netherrack adjacent to nylium converts it into nylium.
If two nylium blocks of different types are present, it chooses the type at random based on how many blocks of each type are around it.
Observers and blocks of redstone now allow placing of ladders and tripwire hooks.

A single redstone wire is now represented as a cross.
Redstone will provide power to blocks on sides it shows a visual connection to, and not do so on those sides without a visual connection.
A wire on top of a block, which is redirected from below, will now power the sides it is redirected to.
Wires that redirect upwards to wires on non-conductive blocks used to only be redirected visually, now this redirection applies to their behavior as well.
A wire that is redirected to go over a block will now always provide power to the block. This is most noticeable when the wire has signal strength 1.
Redstone dust's hitbox now adjusts to its shape.
Redstone dust now visually connects when traveling up soul sand and 8-layer snow stacks.
Redstone dust now visually connects when going up the back (including far-side) of Stairs
Particles are now generated across the entire area of the redstone dust. (Fixed Bug: MC-181566)

Smithing tables now have a GUI use.
Smithing tables can now be used to upgrade diamond gear to netherite
Doors, rails, buttons, torches, pressure plates and redstone can now be placed on a full-block of snow layers.

Soul sand now generates in soul sand valley biomes at the lava level of the lava ocean.
Soul sand with a rail on top will no longer slow-down minecarts.
Doors, buttons, torches, pressure plates and redstone can now be placed on soul sand.
A structure block's maximum size per axis now expands to 48.
TNTs now ignite when hit by any burning projectile.
Vines now play a sound when climbed.

Walls in the middle of a row have longer pillars when stacked vertically.
Block state now uses none, low, and tall for east, west, north, and south directional values.
Snout banner patterns can be found in chests in bastion remnants.
Snout banner patterns have the same function as any other banner pattern.
Pigstep music discs can be found in chests in bastion remnants.
Pigstep music discs have the same function as any other music disc.

Bone meal can now be used to grow kelp, weeping vines, and twisting vines.
Bone meal will now grow fungus, roots, and nether sprouts if it is used on a nylium block.
A fungus can be grown into a huge fungus on its corresponding nylium.

Using a compass on a lodestone creates a lodestone compass, which points to that block.
Compasses can now be enchanted with Curse of Vanishing.

Each tier now has a different speed at which it mines blocks it is effective against.
Hoes can now be enchanted with Efficiency, Fortune, and Silk Touch through the enchanting table.
Hoes are now the appropriate tools for mining hay bales, targets, dried kelp blocks, sponges, wet sponges, leaves, shroomlights, nether wart blocks, and warped wart blocks.

An open space made mostly of soul sand and soul soil.
Basalt pillars span from floor to ceiling.
Nether fossils generate across the valley.
Ash falls through the air.
A light blue glow envelopes the valley.
Ghasts and skeletons traverse the valley.
Biome-exclusive ambient sounds can be heard within the valley.
The music track 'So Below' composed by Lena Raine will play inside this biome.
Soul Sand can be found on this biome at the lava level of the lava ocean.

Warped nylium carpets the cave floor with nether sprouts and warped fungi growing throughout the biome.
Huge warped fungi make up the "trees" of this forest, with shroomlights lighting up their interiors.
Many twisting vines grow upwards from the floor of the biome.
A dark blue fog covers the forest.
Warped spores swirl through the air.
The warped forests are the least hostile places in the Nether.
Endermen can be found more frequently within the forests.
Biome-exclusive ambient sounds can be heard within the forests.

Crimson nylium makes up the floor of the Crimson Forest with nether sprouts, crimson roots, and crimson fungi growing throughout the biome.
Huge crimson fungi grow abundantly throughout the biome, providing crimson stems and shroomlights, as well as nether wart blocks.
Weeping vines will often grow down from the nether wart blocks on the huge crimson fungi.
A red fog covers the entirety of the biome.
Red ashes and particles often flow through the air.
Many hoglins, piglins and zombified piglins can be found spawning within the crimson forest.
The crimson forest has many new, exclusive ambient sounds.
The music track 'Chrysopoeia' composed by Lena Raine will play inside this biome.

Basalt is found in an abundance in this biome.
Patches of blackstone generate inside the basalt formations.
A gray fog covers the deltas.
White ash swirls through the air.
Magma cubes spawn very frequently within the deltas.
The basalt deltas come with a variety of ambient sounds.
The music track 'So Below' composed by Lena Raine will play inside this biome.
The Nether was split into biomes.

The Nether biome is renamed to Nether Wastes.
Piglins and striders now spawn here.
Added new ambient sounds.
The music track 'Rubedo' composed by Lena Raine will play inside this biome.
Generate in the Nether in all biomes except basalt deltas.

Piglins
Magma Cubes
Hoglins
Piglin Brutes

Serves as the home of piglins.
Piglin brutes spawn only in this structure.
Gilded blackstone naturally generates only in this structure, both as one of the blocks that make up the structure and as chest loot.
Nether fossils generate in the Nether and are found exclusively in soul sand valley biomes.
Generate in all biomes in both the Nether and the Overworld. They can spawn underground (partially or fully), underwater, or exposed to the air.

Naturally generated damaged nether portals
Overworld materials in Overworld, Nether in Nether.
Basalt pillars generate in the Nether and are found exclusively in soul sand valley biomes.
Huge crimson fungi and Huge warped fungi
Huge crimson fungi generate in crimson forest and huge warped fungi generate in warped forest

Similar to huge mushrooms
Huge crimson fungi is made from nether wart blocks and crimson stems and huge warped fungi is made from warped wart blocks and warped stems

Soul sand valleys
and Basalt Deltas
Makes the player move faster when on Soul Sand and Soul Soil, and overrides the slowing functionality of the former.
Randomized Trading(-like) system between players and piglins.
To find treasures, the bobber must be cast into water that is at least 5x3x5 blocks.
